1 conv icted of the criminal offenses provided for in paragraphs 2, 4,
2 5, and 6 of subsection A of this section shall be punished in
3 accordance with the corresponding penalties provided for in the
4 Oklahoma Statutes including Section 51.1 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
5 Statutes this title. The provisions of subsection C of this section
6 still applies to the criminal offenses listed in paragraphs 2, 4, 5,
7 and 6 of subsection A of this section.
8 F. All Class D2 criminal offenses shall be punishable by the
9 corresponding fines as provided for in the Oklahoma Statutes.
10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1379.2 of Title 21, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 Any person who boards a school bus without proper authorization
14 or refuses to exit a school bus upon command shall, upon conviction,
15 be guilty of a Class D2 felony punishable by imprisonment pursuant
16 to subsections B through E of Section 20O of Title 21 of the
17 Oklahoma Statutes. For the purposes of this section, “proper
18 authorization” means permission from a school district employee.
19 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
20 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY
